# S2-2: User Profile Page (bio, display name, participation history)

Add full user accounts to Collective Unconscious. The existing anonymous session-token flow (Sprint 1) must remain fully intact — user accounts are an **optional upgrade** on top of it. Users who log in with Google can get a persistent display name, bio, and participation history tied to their real account.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google OAuth credentials needed**: You'll need to create a project in [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/), enable the Google+ API, and add `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` to your [.env](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/.env). The callback URL for local dev will be `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google/callback`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No passwords stored** — per [.antigravityrules](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/.antigravityrules), OAuth only. Users log in exclusively via Google.

> [!NOTE]
> The [Writer](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/middleware/auth.js#74-136) model's `sessionToken` field currently links anonymous sessions to log participation. When a user logs in, we will optionally link their [Writer](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/middleware/auth.js#74-136) records to their [User](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/UserProfilePage.jsx#3-13) account (via a nullable `userId` FK), but this is additive — no existing data is altered.

