### Run existing tests (must stay green)
```bash
cd server && npm test
```
All 5 existing test files (`authMiddleware`, `health`, `logs`, `logs.feed`, `turns`, `schema`) must continue to pass.

### Run new auth tests
```bash
cd server && npm test -- --testPathPattern="auth|users"
```

### Manual Verification
1. Start the server: `cd server && npm run dev`
2. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/google` in your browser
3. Complete the Google OAuth flow
4. After redirect back, hit `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me` — you should see your Google profile info returned as JSON
5. In the client (`cd client && npm run dev`), the Header should show "Sign in with Google" when logged out, and your display name when logged in
